---
import { withBase } from "@/lib/paths";
---

<section class="section-space">
  <div class="page-frame">
    <div class="hero-glow glass-panel rounded-[2.4rem] px-6 py-10 md:px-10 md:py-14">
      <div class="grid gap-8 xl:grid-cols-[1.14fr_0.86fr] xl:items-start">
        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="inline-flex rounded-full border border-sky-500/15 bg-sky-500/8 px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-sky-500">
            Main product site
          </div>
          <h1 class="max-w-3xl text-balance text-4xl font-semibold leading-tight text-ink-950 md:text-6xl">
            Premium Microsoft 365 reporting with a clean, production-grade information architecture.
          </h1>
          <p class="max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-ink-700">
            The site, login flow, legal pages, Jekyll blog, and in-session app experience all feel like one product while still being separated into maintainable architectural boundaries.
          </p>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
            <a href={withBase("/login")} class="rounded-full bg-ink-900 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:bg-ink-800">
              Start at /login
            </a>
            <a
              href={withBase("/blog")}
              class="rounded-full border border-ink-900/10 bg-white/90 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-ink-800 transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:border-ink-900/25"
            >
              Read the blog
            </a>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-2">
            <span class="rounded-full bg-sand-100 px-3 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-700">Read-only</span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-sand-100 px-3 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-700">Zero-storage</span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-sand-100 px-3 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-700">GitHub Pages</span>
            <span class="rounded-full bg-sand-100 px-3 py-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-700">Jekyll blog</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid gap-4">
          <div class="fine-border rounded-[1.8rem] bg-white/92 p-6">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-sky-500">Why the structure matters</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-ink-700">
              Modern SaaS products feel premium when routing, content ownership, and consent flows are deliberate instead of being mixed together in a flat project.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-3 xl:grid-cols-1">
            <div class="fine-border rounded-[1.5rem] bg-white/90 p-5">
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-600">Core metrics</p>
              <p class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-950">Users, licenses, groups</p>
            </div>
            <div class="fine-border rounded-[1.5rem] bg-white/90 p-5">
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-600">Exports</p>
              <p class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-950">CSV, JSON, Excel, HTML</p>
            </div>
            <div class="fine-border rounded-[1.5rem] bg-white/90 p-5">
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.16em] text-ink-600">Publishing</p>
              <p class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-ink-950">Astro + Jekyll</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
